  "subtopic": "Worked Example 25.6",
  "question": "If $X$ has the cdf $F(x) = \\begin{cases} 0, & x < -1 \\\\ \\frac{1}{4}, & -1\\le x < 1 \\\\ \\frac{1}{2}, & 1\\le x < 3 \\\\ \\frac{3}{4}, & 3\\le x < 5 \\\\ 1, & x\\ge 5 \\end{cases}$ find (a) $\\Pr(X\\le 3)$ (b) $\\Pr(X = 3)$ (c) $\\Pr(X < 3)$ (d) $\\Pr(X\\ge 1)$ (e) $\\Pr(-0.4 < X < 4)$ (f) $\\Pr(-0.4\\le X < 4)$ (g) $\\Pr(-0.4 < X\\le 4)$ (h) $\\Pr(-0.4\\le X\\le 4)$ (i) $\\Pr(X = 5)$.",
  "answer": "",
  "explanation": "(a) $\\Pr(X\\le 3) = F(3) = \\frac{3}{4}$. (b) $\\Pr(X = 3) = F(3)-F(3^-) = \\frac{3}{4} - \\frac{1}{2} = \\frac{1}{4}$. (c) $\\Pr(X < 3) = F(3^-) = \\frac{1}{2}$. (d) $\\Pr(X\\ge 1) = 1-F(1^-) = 1-\\frac{1}{4} = \\frac{3}{4}$. (e) $\\Pr(-0.4 < X < 4) = F(4^-)-F(-0.4) = \\frac{3}{4} - \\frac{1}{4} = \\frac{1}{2}$. (f) $\\Pr(-0.4\\le X < 4) = F(4^-)-F(-0.4^-) = \\frac{3}{4} - \\frac{1}{4} = \\frac{1}{2}$. (g) $\\Pr(-0.4 < X\\le 4) = F(4)-F(-0.4) = \\frac{3}{4} - \\frac{1}{4} = \\frac{1}{2}$. (h) $\\Pr(-0.4\\le X\\le 4) = F(4)-F(-0.4^-) = \\frac{3}{4} - \\frac{1}{4} = \\frac{1}{2}$. (i) $\\Pr(X = 5) = F(5)-F(5^-) = 1-\\frac{3}{4} = \\frac{1}{4}$",
  "source": "Finan §25 — Worked Example 25.6"
}